The State of Qatar is providing humanitarian assistance to KwaZulu-Natal. And several ministers are at King Shaka International Airport to welcome the Quatari delegation. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala says the support given by the Qatar government is encouraging. The State of Qatar is providing humanitarian assistance to KZN communities affected by the recent floods. READ: KZN Floods | Humanitarian aid arrives from Qatar Zikalala hopes to continue building relationships with various countries. He said, "it is the humanitarian support which talked to various things that are required when people are affected by floods. The support came from the Qatar government reaching out through the ministers of foreign affairs in SA..." "We been trying  to ensure that we build, good relationships with various countries. We are inspired that they felt that they should come assist us during this time of need."